 : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_3}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">na1</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Cslib/Computability/Automata/NA/Basic.html#Cslib.Automata.NA.FinAcc\">FinAcc</a> <span class=\"fn\">State1</span> <span class=\"fn\">Symbol</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">na2</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Cslib/Computability/Automata/NA/Basic.html#Cslib.Automata.NA\">NA</a> <span class=\"fn\">State2</span> <span class=\"fn\">Symbol</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Cslib/Computability/Automata/NA/Basic.html#Cslib.Automata.NA\">NA</a> (<span class=\"fn\">State1</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Sum\">⊕</a> <span class=\"fn\">State2</span>) <span class=\"fn\">Symbol</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`concat na1 na2` starts by running `na1` and then nondeterministically switches to `na2`\nby identifying an accepting state of `na1` with an initial state of `na2`. If `na1` accepts the\nempty word, it may also start running `na2` from the beginning. Once it starts running `na2`,\nit cannot go back to `na1`. ","docLink":"./Cslib/Computability/Automata/NA/Concat.html#Cslib.Automata.NA.concat","kind":"def","line":23,"name":"Cslib.Automata.NA.concat","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/cslib/blob/7f88669e78c0fa9d9c4f41a397072114cbb9aa7e/Cslib/Computability/Automata/NA/Concat.lean#L23-L33"}}],"imports":["Init","Cslib.Computability.Automata.NA.Total","Cslib.Foundations.Data.OmegaSequence.Temporal"],"instances":[{"className":"Cslib.LTS.Total","name":"Cslib.Automata.NA.FinAcc.instTotalSumUnitFinConcat","typeNames":["Cslib.Automata.NA.toLTS"]}],"name":"Cslib.Computability.Automata.NA.Concat"}